	<h2>Key Principles</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Knowledge is power:</strong> Understanding fork mechanics helps you make better decisions
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Size appropriately:</strong> Only hold what you can afford to lose in worst-case scenarios
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Stay informed:</strong> Regular fork meter checks are part of prudent risk management
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Plan ahead:</strong> Think through fork scenarios before they happen
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Engage with community:</strong> Forks are collective decisions, not just individual ones
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Be flexible:</strong> Adjust your positions and plans as risk levels change
		</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		By following these strategies, you can manage fork risk effectively while still participating
		in Augur's markets.
	</p>
